A devolution event in Katumba, Kitui county, was disrupted by shouting, stick-wielding Tana River herders who live there.It was hastily adjourned. Although the ceremony took place on the Kitui side of the border with Tana River, the herders protested against hoisting the Kitui county flag. They demanded it be lowered and replaced with the Tana River banner.They disrupted the meeting for 15 minutes and armed police were called. The event was attended by Wijir Governor Ahmed Abdullahi who passed the devolution torch to Kitui Governor Julius Malombe.